Parliament has announced that &#8220;appropriate security measures&#8221; will be taken to support African National Congress (ANC) Member of Parliament Dr Makhosi Khoza following a number of threatening messages sent to her.Recently Khoza shared on her Facebook page messages sent to her threatening to kill her because of her stance related to the motion of no confidence vote in President Jacob Zuma.According to a statement by Parliament, Speaker Baleka Mbete previously received a report regarding threats made to Khoza from ANC Chief Whip, Jackson Mthembu.She later referred the matter to the South African Police Service (SAPS) whose assessment confirmed that a threat existed against Khoza and that &#8220;appropriate support must be provided&#8221;.&#8220;In this regard, Parliament is working with SAPS to ensure that the two institutions collaboratively provide the necessary support to Dr Khoza as soon as possible. Dr Khoza will accordingly be advised of the arrangements,&#8221; said parliaments spokesperson Moloto Mothapo in a statement.Khoza, who has been a vocal critic of President Zuma today called on him to step down during Conference for the Future of South Africa hosted by the Ahmed Kathrada Foundation in Randburg, Johannesburg.Parliament today again condemned the threats against Khoza saying &#8220;such actions attempt to interfere with the institution s Constitutional function of carrying out its oversight duties,&#8221;-TNA Reporter